          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin osmium samples were prepared by electrolytic",
                "deposition of the enriched Os-192 on 25-mum Ni-foils",
                " (99.9% pure) chemical purityof used osmium- 99.9%.",
                "Isotopic composition:",
                "84.5% Os-192,",
                "15.2% Os-190,",
                "0.3% Os-189,",
                "the electrolytic deposit of metallic osmium had a  mass",
                "between  1  and 4 mg, which was determined by weighing.",
                "The uniformity of the deposit was checked using a",
                "microscope.   Also the absence of all oxides, which are",
                "coloured, could be confirmed.  A check via proton",
                "activation analysis was done, too."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TTY-C"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The integrated yield of Ir-192 was calculated ,",
                "assuming a 1 hour irradiation with a proton beam of",
                "1 microA."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The model codes ALICE-IPPE and EMPIRE-II.",
                "A comparison of the reactor and cyclotron production",
                "methods is given too."
